t the days go by so pointlessly and stupidly—and these are supposed to be the best, the happiest years of our life. It looks as if I shall soon turn into a hypocrite—I mean, hypochondriac. No, that mustn’t happen.

“Let me get rid of the shackles of love

And let me try to stop thinking!

Replenish, replenish the glasses with wine—

Let me keep drinking and drinking!



